description:
You are an agricultural extension agent preparing a spring planting advisory for Iowa farmers. Research the most recent USDA data for Corn and Soybeans using NASS (nass.usda.gov) and ERS (ers.usda.gov) or WASDE. You must identify Iowa's total production in millions of bushels, the national average yield per acre, and the current estimated average farm price per bushel for both crops. Create a Firefox bookmark folder named 'Crop Planning Research' containing at least 5 relevant USDA pages. Generate a JSON advisory file at ~/Documents/crop_planning_advisory.json using the following structure:

{
  "corn": {
    "iowa_production_bushels_millions": <number>,
    "national_yield_bushels_per_acre": <number>,
    "price_per_bushel_dollars": <number>
  },
  "soybeans": {
    "iowa_production_bushels_millions": <number>,
    "national_yield_bushels_per_acre": <number>,
    "price_per_bushel_dollars": <number>
  },
  "data_year": "YYYY",
  "recommendation": "<Your text advice based on the data>"
}
